        "answer_count": 1,
        "title": "Java: Integer equality check",
        "body": "<p><strong>Case 1:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Integer number = 128;\nInteger number3 = 128;\nSystem.out.println(number == number3);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><strong>Case 2:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Integer number = 127;\nInteger number3 = 127;\nSystem.out.println(number == number3);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>In this case if the value > 127 it returns false but if the value &lt; 128 then it returns true. <\/p>\n\n<p><strong>Can somebody explain why case 1 returns false and case 2 returns true?<\/strong> <\/p>\n",
